name: object-merge
readme:
# object-merge

Creates a new mixin object c which has object a's own properties and object b's . 

## Install

    $ npm install object-merge


  ## Usage

```javascript
var mixin=require('object-merge');
Object.prototype.foobar=function(){};var a = { foo: 'bar' },
b = { bar: 'foos' }; 
mixin(a, b);
// => { foo: 'bar', bar: 'baz' }```

## Tests

    $ npm install
    $ npm test
